 :tx/rationale "ADR-FOUNDATION-032: ONTOLOGICAL SURPRISE — detecting unknown unknowns via observation-schema gap analysis. The deepest gap in the introspective observer: FEGH detects missing BRIDGES between known clusters (known unknowns). But the capability census failure revealed missing CATEGORIES entirely (unknown unknowns). The store had zero :runtime/* datoms — not a sparse cluster, a complete void that spectral partition can't detect. FIX: The daemon watches the stream of agent observations for ontological novelty. Let S = attribute namespaces in schema, O = concept categories in observation text (topic clustering). The ontological gap = O minus S — concepts agents discuss that the store has no schema for. When gap detected, propose schema extension. This IS OBSERVER-6 (ontology discovery) from the three learning loops, connected to the daemon. The mechanism: (1) Topic clustering on :exploration/body text across sessions. (2) Map clusters to nearest schema namespace. (3) Clusters with no nearby namespace = ontological surprise. (4) Surface as: 'NEW CATEGORY DETECTED: agents discuss X but store has no :X/* attributes. Propose schema extension?' This is the system discovering its own blind spots by watching what users care about. It would have auto-generated SCHEMA-RUNTIME-1. Free energy interpretation: standard F measures KL divergence within existing dimensions. Ontological surprise measures the DIMENSIONALITY GAP — states in P(reality) with no representation in Q(model). TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-031, ADR-FOUNDATION-030, OBSERVER-6, C7."
